he preferred form of the name."]},{"name":"Isobelle","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]},{"name":"Isobel","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Isabel ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Isabell Lead was born about 1680, in Edinburgh, Scotland. She had at least 1 daughter with Alexander Gregg."},"et":{"about 1680–":"umbes 1680–Surnud","1680–Male":"1680–Surnud","1697–1770":"1697–1770","1680–Female":"1680–Surnud","6 November 1697":"6. november 1697","1697":"1697","1770":"1770","1680":"1680","about 1680":"umbes 1680","Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland":"Edinburgh, Scotland","Monquhitter, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Monquhitter, Aberdeenshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1680–":"noin 1680–Kuollut","1680–Male":"1680–Kuollut","1697–1770":"1697–1770","1680–Female":"1680–Kuollut","6 November 1697":"6. marraskuuta 1697","1697":"1697","1770":"1770","1680":"1680","about 1680":"noin 1680","Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland":"Edinburgh, Scotland","Monquhitter, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Monquhitter, Aberdeenshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"about 1680–":"environ 1680–Décédée","1680–Male":"1680–Décédé","1697–1770":"1697–1770","1680–Female":"1680–Décédée","6 November 1697":"6 novembre 1697","1697":"1697","1770":"1770","1680":"1680","about 1680":"environ 1680","Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland":"Edinburgh, Écosse","Monquhitter, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Monquhitter, Aberdeenshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Isabell Lead est née environ 1680, à Edinburgh, Écosse. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Alexa